    <div class="post-631 page type-page status-publish hentry" id="post-631">
        
    <div class="page_header">
        <h1>Clean Energy &amp; EST League Table Awards</h1>
    </div>    
     
        <div class="body_text">
            <div class="intro_text">
<p>Bloomberg New Energy Finance&rsquo;s annual League Table Awards honour the leading firms, investors and financial service providers in clean energy and the energy smart technologies sectors. Now in its seventh year, our independent and data-driven awards have become the definitive benchmark for investors and professional service providers across all major asset classes.</p>
</p></div>
<p>Produced annually, the report is the most transparent and comprehensive benchmark for identifying the most active and innovative clean energy investors, project financiers, investment banks, and law firms. The League Tables are based on Bloomberg New Energy Finance&#8217;s authoritative database of financial transactions in these sectors. Data is collected and validated by our global data team and confirmed by the parties involved, making these tables the only comprehensive, objective and fact-based awards in the sector.</p>
<p><a href="http://about.bloomberg.com/pdf/bnef-2011-ye-clean-energy-est-league-tables.pdf" target="_blank">Download the 2011 League Table Results book here.</a></p>
<p class="intro_text_2 margin_top_24">LEAGUE TABLE WINNERS 2011:</p>
<p class="intro_text_2 margin_top_20">Asset Finance</p>
<p><strong>Top Lead Arranger (by total $m amount)</strong><br />
    Federal Financing Bank </p>
<p><strong>Top Syndicated Lender (by total $m amount)</strong><br />
    NIBC </p>
<p><strong>Top Sponsor (by total $m amount)</strong><br />
    NRG Energy </p>
<p><strong>Legal Advisor (by total $m amount)</strong><br />
    Allen &#038; Overy </p>
<p class="intro_text_2 margin_top_20">Mergers &amp; acquisitions</p>
<p><strong>Top Acquire</strong><br />
    EDF </p>
<p class="intro_text_2 margin_top_20">Venture Capital &#038; Private Equity</p>
<p><strong>Top Investor (by total $m deal credit)</strong><br />
    Terra Firma Capital Partners</p>
<p><strong>Top Investor by Number of Disclosed Investments</strong><br />
    Kleiner Perkins Caufield &#038; Byers</p>
<p class="intro_text_2 margin_top_20">Acquisition Advisors</p>
<p><strong>Top M&#038;A / VCPE Financial Advisor</strong><br />
    Credit Suisse</p>
<p><strong>Top M&#038;A / VCPE Legal Advisor</strong><br />
    Linklaters</p>
<p class="intro_text_2 margin_top_20">Public markets</p>
<p><strong>Top Public Markets Lead Manager</strong><br />
    Morgan Stanley</p>
<p><strong>Top Public Markets Co-Lead Manager</strong><br />
    Essence Securities </p>
<p><strong>Top Public Markets Legal Advisor</strong><br />
    Global Law Office </p>
            <div class="clr"></div>
            
        </div> <!-- end body_text -->
